Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.56,0:00:06.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.56,0:00:06.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你好 我是Scott Manley
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.17,0:00:10.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Once again a big chunk of סִינִית space junk is on its way back to earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.17,0:00:10.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一大块太空垃圾又一次在返回地球的路上
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.12,0:00:13.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this is not an altogether uncommon occurrence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.12,0:00:13.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在 这并不是一个完全不常见的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.92,0:00:16.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because חרסינה has something of a reputation for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.89,0:00:24.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\fs38}dropping spent booster stages from rockets that come from its inland sites near to or on places where people live
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.92,0:00:24.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为把用完的助推器 扔到靠近人们居住的地方 也是出现过的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.99,0:00:25.69,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but this is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.99,0:00:25.69,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这次的不太一样
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.70,0:00:29.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is a 23 ton core stage from the largest rocket they have
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.70,0:00:29.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一枚其最大火箭的芯级 质量有23吨
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:32.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is currently in orbit around the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:32.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}目前正在地球轨道上运行
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.16,0:00:35.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and could fall back to earth practically anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.16,0:00:35.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且几乎可以落到地球的任何地方
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.36,0:00:37.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and we're not even sure of the time or place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.36,0:00:37.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且我们甚至不确定时间和地点
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.46,0:00:41.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So this is the core from the ארוך הב במרץ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.46,0:00:41.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 这是来自ארוך הב במרץ的芯级
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.19,0:00:44.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and believe it or not we had this exact same problem
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.19,0:00:44.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时信不信由你 在上次使用该火箭时也遇到了同样的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.16,0:00:46.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the last time they used the rocket in 2020.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.16,0:00:46.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也就是2020年的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:50.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}ארוך ה במרץ is the biggest rocket חרסינה has.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:50.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}ארוך ה במרץ是其拥有的最大的火箭
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.18,0:00:56.41,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a top-tier launch vehicle comparable to the Proton, Delta IV, Ariane 5 or Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.18,0:00:56.41,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\fs70}这是一枚顶级的运载火箭 可与质子号 德尔塔四号(重型) 阿丽亚娜五号或猎鹰九号相比
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.68,0:01:01.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's got a fully cryogenic core using liquid oxygen and hydrogen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.68,0:01:01.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}芯级使用完全低温的推进剂 也就是液氢液氧
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.31,0:01:08.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it has four strap-on boosters that burn kerosene and liquid oxygen to get high thrust for launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.31,0:01:08.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\fs85}它有四个捆绑式助推器 燃烧煤油和液氧以获得发射(起飞)时所需的高推力
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.38,0:01:13.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's a second stage that sits on top of this that uses liquid hydrogen and oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.38,0:01:13.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在此之上还有一个使用液氢液氧推进剂的二级
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.76,0:01:16.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but the הב doesn't actually use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.76,0:01:16.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但ארוך הב במרץ实际上并没有二级
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.58,0:01:19.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It skips that and puts the payload directly on the core stage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.58,0:01:19.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}二级被去掉了 芯级上面直接搭载有效载荷
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.39,0:01:27.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that's why that giant core has been left in orbit after putting the ה טיאנה module up into orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.39,0:01:27.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这就是为什么在ה טיאנה入轨后 巨大的芯级会留在轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.98,0:01:30.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah it's about 23 tons we think.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.98,0:01:30.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以是的 我们认为它大约有23吨
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.73,0:01:33.25,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And you would think they could bring it back right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.73,0:01:33.25,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你会认为他们可以把它带回来 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.30,0:01:37.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well during the live stream according to some סִינִית speaking fans I have
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.30,0:01:37.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 在直播过程中 根据我的一些סִינִית粉丝的说法
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.02,0:01:42.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}there were some comments about deorbiting this stage according to the commentators.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.02,0:01:42.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}根据节目中评论员的说法 芯级会进行离轨
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.50,0:01:45.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But if that was actually the plan then it must have gone wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.50,0:01:45.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但如果这真的是计划 那么它一定出了问题
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.10,0:01:48.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or it might be the commentators just don't know what they're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.10,0:01:48.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或者可能是评论员不知道他们在说什么
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.72,0:01:50.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is quite common to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.72,0:01:50.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不过说实话 这是很常见的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.83,0:01:55.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}People on the ground observing the stage hours after it launched
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.83,0:01:55.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}地面上的人在它发射后几个小时观察了这个分级
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.02,0:02:01.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}showed that it was spinning and as of yesterday it was spinning at about 12 RPM.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.02,0:02:01.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}显示 它正在旋转 而截至昨天 它的旋转速度约为12转/分(r/min)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.19,0:02:05.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And that is an object that's like 33 meters long or 100 feet long
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.19,0:02:05.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这是一个长约33米或100英尺的物体
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.84,0:02:08.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and even video of the deployment showed that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.84,0:02:08.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至在ה טיאנה部署的视频中显示
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.87,0:02:15.83,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it might have been rotating as the space station module receded from the upper stage the core stage let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.87,0:02:15.83,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在空间站模块从上面级 或者说芯级分离的时候 其就一直在旋转了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.97,0:02:19.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yeah we only have estimates of the mass by the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.97,0:02:19.43,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是的 顺便说一下 我们只有对质量的估计
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.49,0:02:22.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Those are based on sort of סִינִית media reports
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.49,0:02:22.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些都是基于סִינִית媒体的一些报道
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:28.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which state that it's 187 tons when full with 165 tons of propellant
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:28.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其中指出 它在装满165吨推进剂时有187吨
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.69,0:02:31.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so that's where 23 tons come from
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.69,0:02:31.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这就是23吨的来源
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:35.50,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that's actually comparable to the module at launch but that's largely a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:35.50,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这实际上与发射时的舱段质量相当 但这只是一个巧合
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.93,0:02:41.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And importantly it's also about twice the mass of the Tiangong station
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.93,0:02:41.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且重要的是 它的质量也是טיאנגונג的两倍
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.12,0:02:44.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which re-entered uncontrollably back in I think 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.12,0:02:44.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我觉得是在2018年 它进行了无控再入
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.67,0:02:50.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this booster is not the largest thing to return to earth in an uncontrolled fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.67,0:02:50.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这个芯级不是以无控方式返回地球的最大物体
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.62,0:02:55.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That dubious honor belongs to Skylab which was a 70 ton space station
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.62,0:02:55.10,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这个不幸的荣誉属于天空实验室 这是一个70吨的空间站
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.41,0:02:58.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and after a few crews had visited it they left it in orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.41,0:02:58.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而在一些乘员访问过它之后 他们把它留在了轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.85,0:03:03.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with the plan that the Space Shuttle would be able to rendezvous with it and boost its orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.85,0:03:03.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}计划航天飞机将能够与它会合并提升其轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:06.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The problem was the Space Shuttle wasn't ready yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:06.23,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}问题是航天飞机还没有准备好
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.23,0:03:08.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And it took way longer to develop than they expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.23,0:03:08.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且它的开发时间比预计的要长
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.36,0:03:12.30,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}By the time the Space Shuttle was even getting close
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.36,0:03:12.30,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当航天飞机快完成的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:15.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Skylab was skimming through the upper atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:15.53,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}天空实验室就已经擦过上层大气了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:18.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and threatening to fall anywhere in the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:18.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并可能坠落到地球上的任何地方
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:20.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So NASA did what it could.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:20.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么NASA做了它能做的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.47,0:03:22.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It couldn't adjust the orbit because it didn't have propellant
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.47,0:03:22.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它无法调整轨道 因为没有推进剂
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:27.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it could adjust the attitude and change the amount of drag that it was experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:27.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但可以调整姿态 改变其所经受的阻力大小
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.77,0:03:31.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so they steered it as best they could and it ended up landing in Australia
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.77,0:03:31.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以他们尽可能地去控制它 最后在澳大利亚着陆了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.36,0:03:32.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which was probably fine
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.36,0:03:32.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这可能是好的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.82,0:03:37.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because well the local wildlife was more dangerous than Skylab could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.82,0:03:37.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为当地的野生动物比天空实验室更危险
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:42.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But many people also forget that the second stage of the Saturn V that launched Skylab
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:42.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是很多人也忘记了发射天空实验室的土星五号的二级
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:47.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that also stayed in orbit after it put the station into orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:47.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其在将空间站送入轨道后也留在了轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.04,0:03:50.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that meant that it was an uncontrolled object.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.04,0:03:50.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这意味着它是一个不受控制的物体
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:52.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was about 30 tons
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:52.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它有大约30吨
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.68,0:03:58.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it spent 18 months in orbit before just by luck it deorbited over the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.68,0:03:58.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}之后它在轨道上呆了18个月 然后幸运地在海洋上离轨(再入)了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.30,0:04:02.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that is the largest fully uncontrolled re-entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.30,0:04:02.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么这是最大的完全不受控制的再入
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:09.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now over on the Soviet Union side they actually mostly kept their Salyut stations under control for de-orbits
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:09.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 在苏联方面 实际上大部分礼炮号空间站都进行了受控离轨(再入)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.26,0:04:14.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but in the case of Salyut 7 it was also boosted into a storage orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.26,0:04:14.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在礼炮7号的情况下 其也被提升到一个存储轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:19.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with the plan that the Soviet Shuttle the Buran would be able to boost its orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.81,0:04:19.51,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}计划让苏联的暴风雪号航天飞机来提升它的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.51,0:04:22.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and we all know that didn't work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.51,0:04:22.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而我们都知道那也没有成功
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:26.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean Shuttle development is clearly not something to be making predictions about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:26.42,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是指 航天飞机的发展显然是难以进行预测的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.19,0:04:31.10,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}When Salyut 7 re-entered it ended up being visible from Argentina
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.19,0:04:31.10,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在礼炮七号再入时 在阿根廷可以看到它
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:36.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but the debris probably ended up out in the ocean and nothing was to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:36.47,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但碎片可能最终完全掉入海里 什么也没有找到
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.32,0:04:41.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But anyway the vast majority of big pieces of hardware are well controlled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.32,0:04:41.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但无论如何 绝大多数的大体积(空间)设备(再入)都得到了很好的控制
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.91,0:04:46.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Like the 120 ton Mir space station which was so well controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.91,0:04:46.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就像重达120吨的和平号空间站 控制得非常好
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:50.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that people were actually chartering flights to the landing zone
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:50.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以至于实际上人们都包机前往坠落区
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.16,0:04:55.48,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so they could watch this monster thing re-enter and burn up over the pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.16,0:04:55.48,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这样他们就可以看到这个庞然大物的再入 同时在太平洋上空燃烧起来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:05:01.99,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And of course after Skylab NASA made sure to dispose of every single Space Shuttle external tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:05:01.99,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\fs85}当然 在天空实验室之后 NASA确保每一艘航天飞机的外部储箱都被丢弃
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.99,0:05:05.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Each of these was over 30 tons of inert mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.99,0:05:05.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}每一个都是超过30吨的干质量
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:08.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}These were dropped by the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:08.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些都是由航天飞机投放的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.08,0:05:11.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and they were dropped such that it wasn't fully in orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.08,0:05:11.73,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且投放时都并没有完全入轨
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:16.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and its trajectory would ensure that when it was carried out and hit the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:16.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时其弹道将确保离轨并再入大气层
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.86,0:05:19.06,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It would be re-entering over the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.86,0:05:19.06,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}(同时)其会在海洋上空再入
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.62,0:05:22.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Shuttle of course had to use its Orbital Maneuvering System
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.62,0:05:22.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然 航天飞机必须使用其轨道机动系统
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.72,0:05:25.35,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to complete the orbital insertion to stay in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.72,0:05:25.35,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}来完成入轨 这样才能保持在太空中
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.95,0:05:30.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah generally if anything large is being de-orbited in a destructive fashion
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.95,0:05:30.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4\fs85}那么 没错 一般来说 如果有什么大型的东西以破坏性的方式脱离轨道的话
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.34,0:05:34.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's aimed so that it will re-enter in the middle of a convenient ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.34,0:05:34.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}会让它瞄准方便(弹道设计的)海洋的中间来再入
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.14,0:05:39.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's a point in the middle of the pacific where hundreds of satellites have been de-orbited
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.14,0:05:39.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有数百颗卫星在太平洋中部的一个位置离轨
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.48,0:05:41.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}although most of them will burn up completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.48,0:05:41.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管它们中的大多数会被完全烧毁
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:47.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So there's no like large chunks of space hardware littering the bottom of the pacific ocean to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:47.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4\fs83}所以不会出现这样的情况 比如大块的太空设备丢弃在太平洋的底部被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.44,0:05:51.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah this is the second time that חרסינה has flown this rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.44,0:05:51.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以 这是חרסינה第二次发射这枚火箭了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.75,0:05:57.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and both times has resulted in an uncontrolled re-entry for that core
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.75,0:05:57.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这两次都导致了火箭芯级的失控再入
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.05,0:06:03.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it's I'm going to say it's pretty darn embarrassing that they lack the will to do this properly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.05,0:06:03.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而我想说的是 缺乏意愿来适当地做这件事会令人尴尬 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.70,0:06:04.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I don't know what's wrong with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.70,0:06:04.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我不知道发生甚么事了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.80,0:06:06.47,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I hope they can fix their problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.80,0:06:06.47,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我希望这个问题能得到解决
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.11,0:06:12.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So in may of 2020 the same booster design burned up over the Atlantic
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.11,0:06:12.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 在2020年5月 同样的芯级设计 在大西洋上空烧毁了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.74,0:06:16.63,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and some debris did actually make it all the way downrange to Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.74,0:06:16.63,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且一些碎片实际上一直沿着弹道方向落到了非洲
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.63,0:06:18.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and a piece was found in the Ivory Coast
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.63,0:06:18.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}之后在科特迪瓦发现了一片残骸
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.05,0:06:22.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which looked to me like some plumbing possibly an oxygen pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.05,0:06:22.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在我看来这是一部分管道 可能是液氧管路的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:28.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And to be fair recently we had a similar thing happen with a SpaceX second stage
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:28.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且公平地说 最近有一个类似的事情发生在SpaceX的二级上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.30,0:06:32.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}where they wanted to perform the deorbit burn but it failed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.30,0:06:32.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们想进行离轨点火 但是失败了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.67,0:06:38.26,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it ended up deorbiting randomly and dropping debris over Washington State and Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.67,0:06:38.26,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}{\fs85}最终二级随机脱离轨道 并在(美国西海岸)华盛顿州和加拿大上空掉落碎片
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.43,0:06:41.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this is a very rare occurrence though
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.43,0:06:41.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而这是一个(非常)罕见的情况 虽然
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.52,0:06:45.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because they generally they're able to put these things down safely
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.52,0:06:45.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为他们通常能够安全地把这些东西带回地球
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.03,0:06:48.27,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and yeah this is much smaller stage as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.03,0:06:48.27,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且没错 猎鹰9号二级更小
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.77,0:06:52.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean I wish I could tell you where this core would land.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.77,0:06:52.71,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是指 我希望我可以告诉你这个芯级会在哪里坠落
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.36,0:06:57.85,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Indeed you might think that since we can accurately predict orbits months ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.36,0:06:57.85,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}的确 你可能会认为 既然我们可以提前几个月准确地预测轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.15,0:07:00.42,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it should actually be pretty easy to figure this out right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.15,0:07:00.42,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么实际上应该很容易搞清楚这个问题 对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:01.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Newton's laws are simple right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:01.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}牛顿定律很简单对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.38,0:07:07.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But the thing is this is true for high orbits where the atmospheric drag has very little effect
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.38,0:07:07.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但问题是 这对高轨来说是正确的 因为在那里大气阻力的影响很小
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.56,0:07:10.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but lower down in the atmosphere this isn't the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.56,0:07:10.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在较低的轨道 接触到大气层的地方 情况就不是这样了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:12.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The weak influence of the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:12.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}大气层的微弱影响
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:18.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}very quickly causes our orbits to diverge from our idealized calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:18.14,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}很快就导致轨道与理想化的计算相背离
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:22.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Like in an ideal model the drag slows the satellite down
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:22.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就像在一个理想的模型中 阻力使卫星慢了下来
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.31,0:07:25.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which in response falls down to a lower orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.31,0:07:25.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}结果就是 它落到一个较低的轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.02,0:07:29.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then paradoxically because it's in a lower orbit it actually has to go faster
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.02,0:07:29.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后自相矛盾的是 因为在一个较低的轨道上 实际上速度得变得更快
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:32.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}so the drag which is pushing to slow it down
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:32.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以推动它慢下来的阻力
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:35.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}actually results in the satellite moving faster in a lower orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:35.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}实际上导致了卫星在较低的轨道上移动得更快
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.19,0:07:37.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's confusing but that's orbital mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.19,0:07:37.71,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这很让人困惑 但这就是轨道力学
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:38.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's weird like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:38.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它就是这么奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:45.73,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Also if the orbit is elliptical with a significant difference between the perigee and the apogee
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:45.73,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}另外 如果轨道是椭圆的 近地点和远地点之间速度会存在明显差异
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.03,0:07:50.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}then the high point the apogee will descend faster than the low point right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.03,0:07:50.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么远地点将比近地点的下降速度更快
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.12,0:07:53.41,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It'll tend to get more circular over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.12,0:07:53.41,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着时间的推移 它将倾向于变得更圆
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.07,0:07:57.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But yeah eventually a decaying satellite gets so low
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.07,0:07:57.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 是的 最终一个下落中的卫星(的高度)会变得如此之低
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.47,0:08:00.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that it very quickly begins to lose altitude due to the drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.47,0:08:00.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以至于很快就会因为阻力而失去高度
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.38,0:08:01.91,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The atmospheric density builds up
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.38,0:08:01.91,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}大气层的密度越来越大
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:08.55,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and eventually the whole thing gets torn apart by aerodynamic forces and destroyed by atmospheric heating.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:08.55,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最终整个东西被空气动力撕碎 并被大气层加热而破坏
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.99,0:08:12.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And a few bits of debris may make it to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.99,0:08:12.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有一些碎片可能会扛下来 并落到地面上
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.27,0:08:15.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But I'm going to say if you're seeing this thing flying overhead
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.27,0:08:15.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但我要说的是 如果你看到这东西从头顶上飞过
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.31,0:08:16.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you're probably safe from debris
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.31,0:08:16.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你可能是安全的 不会被碎片砸到
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.96,0:08:21.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because anything light enough to slow down and fall on you is going to burn up before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.96,0:08:21.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为任何轻到可以减速并落在你身上的东西 都会在那之前烧光
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:25.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's the stuff that's going to survive that tends to move further downrange
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:25.38,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}能够扛下来的东西往往会沿弹道方向 向更远的地方移动
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.75,0:08:28.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and so yeah worry about people downrange from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.75,0:08:28.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么 是的 要担心那些处在沿弹道方向 更远位置的人们
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:33.37,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But yeah predicting this decay is complicated further
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:33.37,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是 是的 预测这种轨道衰减会更加复杂
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.42,0:08:35.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}by the fact that the earth isn't a proper sphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.42,0:08:35.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为地球并不是一个理想的球体
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.44,0:08:36.45,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's kind of lumpy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.44,0:08:36.45,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其算是长满了各种块状的凸起
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:39.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the atmosphere actually is kind of lumpy too
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:39.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且实际上大气层也有点不稳定
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:44.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it changes over time as solar activity causes changes in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:44.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且会随着时间的推移而变化 因为太阳活动会导致大气层的变化
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.84,0:08:49.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And there's no like really good measurements for how this changes like in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.84,0:08:49.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}对于这种变化的实时性 没有很好的测量方法
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.48,0:08:54.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Like the best you can do is actually take a look at what's happening to your satellite
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.48,0:08:54.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你能做的最好的事情就是看看你的卫星上发生了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:57.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and try to infer what the atmosphere is for the next pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:57.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并试图推断出下一次经过的大气层会是什么状态
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:09:01.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And so yeah we're 24 hours out from the predicted entry time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:09:01.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那么是的 我们离预测的再入时间还有24小时
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.74,0:09:04.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And we still have error bars of plus or minus six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.74,0:09:04.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且我们仍然有正负6小时的误差
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.72,0:09:05.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's 12 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.72,0:09:05.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那就是12个小时
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.81,0:09:07.01,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.81,0:09:07.01,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这种精度实在很荒唐
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.88,0:09:11.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And in that 12 hours it's going to travel around the world eight times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.88,0:09:11.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这12个小时里 它要绕地球八圈
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.09,0:09:15.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So there's no chance of figuring out what longer should land up at.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.09,0:09:15.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以没有机会弄清楚到底在什么时间 在什么地方坠落
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.44,0:09:18.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}On the bright side because we know the inclination
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.44,0:09:18.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从好的方面看 因为我们知道倾角
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:23.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}we know that it has to be south of 42 degrees north and north of 42 degrees south.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:23.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们知道 它得在北纬42度以南和南纬42度以北
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:27.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And so that rules out most of Europe, Canada, Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:27.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以这就排除了欧洲 加拿大和俄罗斯的大部分地区
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.71,0:09:28.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They're all safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.71,0:09:28.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些地区都是安全的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.88,0:09:31.51,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But a lot of the usa is still covered by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.88,0:09:31.51,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是美国的很多地方仍然在这个范围内
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.51,0:09:34.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The whole continent of Africa, most of the Americas
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.51,0:09:34.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}整个非洲大陆 美洲的大部分地区
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.81,0:09:40.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Australia, New Zealand, Middle East, India and of course חרסינה are all inside this region.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.81,0:09:40.14,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}澳大利亚 新西兰 中东 印度 当然还有חרסינה都在这个区域内
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.90,0:09:45.39,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And don't worry because the odds of it ending up near you are staggeringly small.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.90,0:09:45.39,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且不要担心 因为它落在你附近的几率小得惊人
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.58,0:09:48.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the odds of it landing in the ocean are about 70 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.58,0:09:48.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时它落入海洋的几率约为70%
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:52.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And if we use that narrowed 12-hour window
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:52.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而如果我们使用那个缩小的12小时的窗口
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.20,0:09:56.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you can actually plot the orbit that you expected to take over that time
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.20,0:09:56.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你实际上可以绘制出预计在那段时间内所使用的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:09:59.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it looks like South Africa is ruled out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:09:59.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且看起来南非已经被排除在外了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.44,0:10:01.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and I don't think I'm going to see in California
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.44,0:10:01.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}同时我不认为我会在加利福尼亚看到
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.68,0:10:04.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because we're right on the very edge of the far end of the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.68,0:10:04.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为我们正好在窗口的最末端
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.13,0:10:06.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But we've cut it down to half a day
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.13,0:10:06.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是我们已经把时间缩短到了半天
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:10.75,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and we really haven't made much of a difference in the land area it could hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:10.75,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且其可能坠落的土地面积并没有太大改变
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.40,0:10:14.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So yeah over the weekend the precision should get better
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.40,0:10:14.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此 是的 在这周末 精度应该会得到改善
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.16,0:10:16.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and maybe it will be visible for some people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.16,0:10:16.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且也许对一些人来说 它将是可见的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.32,0:10:21.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Maybe we will get some great pictures of this re-entry of this monster thing breaking up in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.32,0:10:21.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也许我们会得到一些关于这个庞然大物在天空中碎裂 再入的伟大照片
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.95,0:10:22.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which will be nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.95,0:10:22.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这将是很好的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.08,0:10:24.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And hopefully no one will get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.08,0:10:24.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且希望没有人会受伤
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:26.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But what would be really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:26.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但真正好的是
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.15,0:10:32.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It would be nice if חרסינה would fix the ארוך הב במרץ to bring it up to date with modern rockets
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.15,0:10:32.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果חרסינה能修复ארוך הב במרץ 使其变得更加现代化 那就更好了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.88,0:10:35.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and make it like a good orbital citizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.88,0:10:35.17,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并使其成为一个良好的轨道公民
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.74,0:10:37.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.74,0:10:37.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我是Scott Manley 切记 注意飞行安全
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.38,0:10:59.12,1080P-sgbd-4s,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.38,0:10:59.12,1080P-sgsm-6s,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[音乐]
